10. Sit: A. 4403 B. 2783 G. 2643 H. 559. 33 W. 483.— Scipio: P. Cornelius Scipio Africanus Major, the victor in the battle of Zama, which closed the second Punic war in 202 ΒΕ. 11. Italia: notice the unusual omission of the preposition— alter Africanus: i.e. P. Cornelius Scipio Aemilianus Africanus Minor. He was the son of the Paulus mentioned inl. 14 and grandson by adoption of Scipio Africanus Major, and distinguished himself in the third Punic war by the destruction of Carthage in 146 B.C-; and by the destruction of Numantia in Spain in 133 B.C.
